can i point two domain names to the same dns name server i have domain names that i want to point to the same web host i have of them pointed to the dns name server and it is working the other is pointed to the same dns name server but it gives me a error the page cannot be found it's been over hours since i set the dns name server on that domain name it seems like this should work does something about the internet or maybe my web host not allow this yes you can point domain names to the same host the only thing you need to keep in mind is that there should be different accounts for the domain names on your host hosting accounts for different domain names on server this is usually practiced as share hosting or reseller hosting Anti-virus software Computer virus Spyware Malware Trojan horse (computing) Windows XP Filename extension Kazaa Blue screen of death Mozilla Firefox E-mail spam Computer security ITunes Stopping e-mail abuse Windows 2000 ILOVEYOU Rootkit Mydoom Gmail Files-11 Microsoft Windows Btrieve Windows registry Windows API IPod Macromedia Flash BitTorrent MediaMax CD-3 Macintosh Finder AOL Instant Messenger Commodore 64 File Allocation Table Windows Server 2003 MDAC Virtual memory Internet Explorer Common Unix Printing System Microsoft Opera (web browser) Spybot - Search & Destroy Ajax (programming) Proxy server Emacs COM file Uniform Resource Locator Web crawler Ebook Warez Object Desktop Mouse (computing) Wget USB flash drive Microsoft .NET Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol Peer-to-peer MSN Messenger Concurrent Versions System HyperCard HyperText Transfer Protocol Enterprise content management OpenBSD GNU General Public License PlayStation Portable Copyleft Dialer Pretty Good Privacy AmigaOS Web browser Screenshot Steam (content delivery) Comparison of web browsers Cascading Style Sheets NTFS File system Mozilla Application Suite Patch (computing) Microsoft AntiSpyware Floppy disk Windows Me Digital rights management OS/2 E-mail Screensaver Website 